The course supports the writing of thesis in Estonian. All independent work done in the course is related to the topic of student's thesis. 
The course is divided into two modules.
1. Communication skills in writing: general principles of academic text, reference, citation, reference management, discipline-specific language, discipline-specific information research, process oriented writing, sources of practical language planning, professional text.
2. Communication skills in speaking: general principles of spoken language, public speaking, preparing and giving a presentation.
Orthography topics are embedded in other topics and are addressed throughout the course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to improve the communication skills in writing and speaking of undergraduate students of the Faculty of Science and Technology and to support students in writing their thesis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the students: - follow the guidelines of their speciality or institute and the principles of academic text when compiling the thesis; - apply the principles of process oriented writing in order to develop their writing skills; - are able to find relevant information about orthography from the practical language planning sources; - apply the main features of plain language; - use effective techniques when giving a presentation.
